ReportText: CLINICAL DATA: Cough, wheezing, and shortness of breath for the past week; history of asthma, nonsmoker. EXAM: CHEST 2 VIEW COMPARISON: PA and lateral chest x-ray of [DATE] FINDINGS: The lungs are mildly hyperinflated. There is no focal infiltrate. There is no pleural effusion. The heart and pulmonary vascularity are normal. The mediastinum is normal in width. The bony thorax is unremarkable. IMPRESSION: Mild hyperinflation may be voluntary or may reflect acute bronchitis. There is no pneumonia nor other acute cardiopulmonary abnormality. Electronically Signed By: [[PERSONALNAME]] [[PERSONALNAME]] M.D. Electronically Signed By: [[PERSONALNAME]] On: 06/12/2016 12:43
